  "signature": "ed25519:9b2e4f7a1c3d6e0f8b5a2c4d7e1f3a6b9c2e5f8a1b4d7e0f3a6c9b2e5f8a1b4",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (Gradation 2).",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 is a commercially validated FEA solver with documented V&V procedures and ISO 9001-certified QMS. FDA-internal solver instances are maintained under 21 CFR Part 820 software controls. All simulation scripts are version-controlled in Git with peer-reviewed commit history. Achieved Gradation 3 — formal QMS with documented test protocols and traceability matrix."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (Gradation 2).",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems from ASME V&V 10.1 Appendix A were reproduced using the Ansys solver configuration employed in this study. Patch test and cantilever beam benchmarks confirmed element formulation correctness. Convergence of iterative solvers verified against analytical solutions for linear elastic problems analogous to the pedicle screw geometry. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (Gradation 3). Mesh convergence study required with Richardson extrapolation or equivalent.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed on the pedicle screw shank and rod interface regions (coarse: ~85k elements, medium: ~210k, fine: ~520k). Richardson extrapolation yielded a grid convergence index (GCI) of 1.4% for peak von Mises stress at the screw-rod junction. Final production mesh (medium density) used for all ensemble runs. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error assessment was considered beyond the scope of the current submission. The solver vendor documentation was cited as sufficient evidence of solver accuracy; no independent residual convergence analysis or iterative error quantification was performed for the specific nonlinear contact configurations used in this model. This factor was not formally evaluated against the V&V 40 gradation scale."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "rationale": "Use error was considered beyond the scope of this credibility assessment. The modeling team noted that simulation inputs were prepared by experienced analysts and that internal review procedures were in place, but no formal use-error analysis, independent model audit, or structured checklist review against V&V 40 Table 5-1 gradation criteria was conducted. The factor is therefore not assessed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (Gradation 3). Model form selection must be justified with reference to physics and prior literature.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic continuum FEA with surface-to-surface frictional contact (μ=0.3, augmented Lagrange) was selected based on published literature confirming elastic response dominates below yield for Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screws under F1717 loading. Material nonlinearity was incorporated via bilinear isotropic hardening for post-yield behavior. Model form choice supported by three independent peer-reviewed studies. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (Gradation 3). Material properties and geometric inputs must be traceable to measurements or certified material data.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties (E=114 GPa, ν=0.34, σ_y=880 MPa) sourced from certified mill certificates for the specific lot used in bench testing. Screw geometry digitized from CMM measurements of production implants (n=3 screws measured; dimensional variation <0.02 mm). UHMWPE block properties from supplier datasheet confirmed by independent tensile coupon testing. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (Gradation 2). Test samples must be representative of the simulated device.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes). All screws drawn from the same production lot as the CMM-measured implants used to define FEA geometry. Construct assembly followed ASTM F1717 standard procedures with documented torque values. Inter-laboratory variability characterized; coefficient of variation <5% for stiffness. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (Gradation 3). Multiple loading conditions or boundary condition variations required.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single loading condition (static compression-bending per ASTM F1717 at 0.5 mm/min crosshead speed, room temperature). Although this condition is standardized and clinically motivated, only one test configuration was evaluated. No variation in offset distance, loading rate, or temperature was explored. Gradation 2 achieved — below the required Gradation 3. This shortfall is noted as a known gap in the credibility assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (Gradation 3). FEA boundary conditions must demonstrably replicate experimental fixture constraints.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions were mapped directly to experimental fixture geometry: inferior UHMWPE block fully encastred at base, superior block loaded via rigid coupling to actuator attachment point. Offset distance (62 mm per F1717) confirmed by caliper measurement and replicated exactly in FEA geometry. Friction coefficient at screw-block interface estimated from independent tribology tests and confirmed via sensitivity analysis (±20% μ changes QoI by <2%). Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (Gradation 3). Quantitative comparison metric with uncertainty must be reported.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. Validation metric E/uval computed per ASME V&V 10.1 Section 5. Results: stiffness E/uval=1.31, yield force mean error=6.2%, force-at-40mm mean error=7.8%. All metrics within pre-specified acceptance bounds (<10% error, E/uval<1.96). Experimental uncertainty propagated from load cell calibration (±0.5%), displacement transducer (±0.1 mm), and inter-laboratory variability. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (Gradation 2). QoIs must be clinically and mechanically relevant to the COU.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to clinical performance: stiffness governs load sharing with the spine, yield force indicates structural integrity margin, and force at 40 mm displacement captures post-yield ductile behavior relevant to fatigue life prediction. All three QoIs are used in FDA 510(k) substantial equivalence determinations for pedicle screw systems. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level (Gradation 3). Validation activities must closely match the COU in geometry, loading, and material.",
      "rationale": "Validation testing used the identical screw design (non-cannulated 7.5 mm), identical material lot, identical ASTM F1717 test protocol, and identical loading direction as the COU. Two-laboratory design strengthens external validity. The only deviation from clinical COU is use of UHMWPE surrogate vertebral bodies rather than cadaveric bone — a standard and accepted simplification for F1717 standardized testing. Gradation 3 achieved."
    }
  ],
